OL,3,C'We couldn't have stopped Valdo
OL,4,CCalocane killing that night,' says
OL,5,Cpolice chief
OL,7,F"There was a huge, and really visible
OL,8,Foutpouring of grief, and there was a
OL,9,Fvisible outpouring of emotion, and I
OL,10,Fthink really importantly the city, in
OL,11,Fparticular, came together. You know,
OL,12,Fpeople were talking about it, people
OL,13,Fwere phoning in with support, people
OL,14,Fwere supporting each other across all
OL,15,Fthe communities of Nottingham."
OL,17,FMr Griffin says he doesn't think he'll
OL,18,Fever forget the vigil that day.
